  <div class="header" id="simulation_intro">
    <h3>Simulation</h3>
    <p>
    The US Air Force estimates it could save about $1.7 billion over five years by reducing flying hours by 5 percent and shifting more of its pilot and crew training to simulators.

    The US Navy believes that a roughly $500 million investment in flight simulators over seven years could lower annual aviation training costs by $119 million.

    To realize these savings, the skills learned in these simulators must transfer to real life situations.
    High accuracy assets for simulation are critical to create the realisim required for the
    actions practiced in the simulator to translate to real life
    performance.
    </p>

    <p>
    Rockwell-Collins is one of the leaders in the 10 billion global military simulation and virtual training market, creating high end flight simulators, allowing more cockpit time, lower risk and enabling millions in cost savings.

    To get the high accuracy georeferenced basemaps for their industry
    leading Griffen Dome flight simulator, Rockwell-Collins
    turned to Pacific Geomatics.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="gap gap-100"> </div>
  <div class="content" id="pacgeo_process">
    <p>
      We begin by very careful searches of available imagery
      and elevation data. We partner with all of the major satellite
      operators and optimise our searches for the best available
      imagery to complete a specific project. For very large areas,
      we often combine 50cm imagery from multiple satellites to
      create the best seamless image dataset possible.
    </p>

  </div>
  <div class="gap gap-100"></div>
  <div id="singapore_before"></div>
  <div id="singapore_after"></div>
  <div class="gap gap-100"></div>
  <div class="content">
    <p>
      We match both the position and color of our imagery to a
      client’s pre-existing data. We layer multiple dates to patch
      clouds and shadows while maintaining the integrity of Nav
      aids in the imagery. We eliminate all artifacts that detract
      from the desired reality. Haze correction is applied as
      required and special attention is given to blending water
      surface features and water color. If required we provide
      custom masks for water, vegetation, and other materials. We
      blend color and resolution to provide a seamless transition
      between high and low resolution data sets.
    </p>
    <h3>Positioning</h3>
    <p>

      As a final step we correctly position all elements in the dataset.
      Corrections of this sort are small, but critical to ensure that
      reflexes trained in the simulator are not subtly off leading to
      real world accidents.
    </p>

